tasks.description:
Create the plugin SDK types and interfaces in src/plugin/types.ts. This is the foundation everything else builds on.

Define these interfaces:

1. `ColumnDef` — { name: string, type: 'string' | 'number' | 'boolean' | 'json' | 'datetime', description?: string }
2. `KeyColumn` — { name: string, operators: string[] (default ['=']), required: 'required' | 'optional' | 'any_of' }
3. `HydrateFunc` — (ctx: QueryContext, row: Record<string, any>) => Promise<Record<string, any>>
4. `ListFunc` — (ctx: QueryContext) => AsyncGenerator<Record<string, any>>
5. `GetFunc` — (ctx: QueryContext) => Promise<Record<string, any> | null>
6. `TableDef` — { name: string, columns: ColumnDef[], keyColumns?: KeyColumn[], list: ListFunc, get?: GetFunc, hydrate?: { [columnName: string]: HydrateFunc }, description?: string }
7. `PluginDef` — { name: string, version: string, tables: TableDef[], connectionConfigSchema?: Record<string, { type: string, required?: boolean, description?: string, default?: any }> }
8. `QueryContext` — { connection: ConnectionConfig, quals: Qual[], columns: string[], limit?: number }
9. `Qual` — { column: string, operator: string, value: any }
10. `ConnectionConfig` — { name: string, plugin: string, config: Record<string, any> }
11. `CacheEntry<T>` — { data: T[], timestamp: number, ttl: number }
12. `RateLimitConfig` — { maxPerSecond?: number, maxPerMinute?: number, maxConcurrent?: number }

Also create src/plugin/index.ts that re-exports everything.

Update src/types.ts to import and re-export from src/plugin/types.ts for backward compat.

